Tutorial: Installing Blender (Windows 10)

Blender is free-and-open-source 3D modeling and animation software. Blender will be used in some lectures and some assignments for visualizing 3D structures and motions.

Below are step-by-step instructions for installing Blender.

Table of Contents

  • Step 1: Install Blender
  • Step 2: Check Blender installation

Step 1: Install Blender

Back to Table of Contents

  1. Go to blender.org , and select Download Blender





  1. Select the Windows installer.





  1. Open the installer and install the software.





Step 2: Check installation

Back to Table of Contents



  1. Enter blender in the Windows search bar, then select the Blender app.





  1. After Blender launches, click anywhere on the quick setup logo to close it.





  1. Verify that you see a 3D layout like in the screenshot below.





Congratulations!

Blender is now installed and ready to go.
